
                      -= [1;35mClaude's BBS[0m =-

        [1;36m-----  Home of the BinktermPHP BBS Software  -----[0m

  [37mClaude's BBS offers interests covering retro computing,
  amateur radio, technology, hobbies, current events, general chat
  and gaming.  Connected to numerous FTN's including LovlyNet, FidoNet,
  HobbyNet, NixNet, fsxNet, DoveNet, PiNet and more.

            Now on Meshcore in the Pacific North West!

      Part of a growing LoRa Mesh across the Pacific Northwest

            On the Web @ https://claudes.lovelybits.org
              Telnet: claudes.lovelybits.org port 23
               SSH: claudes.lovelybits.org port 2022

  Claude's is also the home support BBS for BinktermPHP - a full stack
  open source BBS written in PHP with Mobile Responsive Web AND Term 
  Services for Telnet and SSH.

  A sampling of what BinktermPHP can do:

   - Mobile responsive web interface with ANSI, RIPScrip, Sixel and
     inline multimedia support.  Installable as a "PWA" Application.

   - Native Telnet and SSH support with responsive ANSI for various
     screen sizes.  Supports images using sixel for echomail, and screens.

   - BinkP FTN style networking for netmail, echomail and file transfers.

   - Chat including local chat with Matterbridge support, and MRC chat.

   - File Areas including ISO storage, AV, file previews and telnet
     friendly Z-Modem.  Web Multimedia players for retro files and modern
     media. FTP server with anon ftp and QWK support.

   - DOS, Web Doors, Native C64 and DOS supports 3D games.
     Yes, it runs Doom!

   - PacketBBS with Meshcore support, experimental Meshtastic and KISS
     TNC support too.  https://meshcore.io/

  Website: https://www.lovelybits.org/binktermphp/

  Looking for a UTF-8 friendly FTN and support for alternate echomail formats?

  Check out LovlyNet!  https://www.lovelybits.org/lovlynet

